Consider the following system of linear equations:
\begin{align*}
5x + 3y &= 7\\
10x + 6y &= 14.2\\
\end{align*}
Convert the system into an augmented matrix and use Gaussian elimination to solve the system. If the resulting matrix after applying row operations is ${\begin{bmatrix}
1 & 0 \\ 
0 & 1
\end{bmatrix}}$, what is the solution of the system?
